# 🧠 What Batching Really Means (Mentally)

Batching means:

    setState()
    setState()
    setState()
      ↓
    ONE render
    ONE reconciliation
    ONE DOM update

Without batching:

    setState → render → DOM
    setState → render → DOM
    setState → render → DOM 💥

React avoids the second scenario.

***

# 🧠 What Scheduling Really Means

Scheduling means React asks:

*   Is this urgent?
*   Is the user interacting?
*   Can I wait?
*   Can I interrupt this render?

This is why:

*   Input stays responsive
*   Transitions feel smooth
*   Large renders don’t block the UI

***

